def: Resembling a boy in a manners or opinions; belonging to a boy;childish; trifling; puerile.A boyish, odd conceit. Baillie.
Boar hunting; -- so called by Anglo-Indians. [Colloq.]Tackeray.
A combining form used in anatomy to indicate connection with,or relation to, the temple, or temporal bone; as, temporofacial.
A tubelike marking, occuring in sandstone and other strata.
A grove of shrubs or low trees under taller ones. Wordsworth.
Calling for notice; compelling attention; notorious; heinous;as, a crying evil.Too much fondness for meditative retirement is not the crying sin ofour modern Christianity. I. Taylor.
Wearing, or entitled to wear, a coronet; of noble birth orrank.
